SIMPLE: truelove
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Truelove
<hw>True"love`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
really beloved.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant. See
<er>Paris</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An unexplained word occurring in Chaucer, meaning,
perhaps, an aromatic sweetmeat for sweetening the breath.</def>
<rj><au>T. R. Lounsbury.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Under his tongue a <qex>truelove</qex> he bore.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Truelove knot</b></col>, <cd>a complicated, involved knot
that does not readily untie; the emblem of interwoven affection or
engagement; -- called also <altname>true-lover's
knot</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trueness</ent>⟦br⟧
